name: Australia Women vs India Women
summary: Australia's dominance continued as they secured a 122-run victory against India in the second women's One-Day International (ODI) match. The third ODI saw a spirited India put up a fight, with Smriti Mandhana scoring a century, but Australia ultimately triumphed by 83 runs. Australia's dominance was further displayed in the first and third ODIs, with a five-wicket and 110-run victory respectively. Notably, Beth Mooney (125*), Tahlia McGrath (114*), and Annabel Sutherland (110) registered centuries for Australia, while Jess Jonassen claimed five wickets in the third ODI. These results solidified Australia's series victory, with India unable to secure a win despite a valiant effort from Mandhana.
